 Lesson 3 : Action Verbs  
ʔibəš  walk  
təlawil  run 
gʷədil  sit 
kiis stand  
ʔitut sleep  
ʔəɬəd eat 
qʷuʔqʷaʔdid drink

Question words:  
lədxʷčad əxʷ čəxʷ Where are you going?  
stab kʷi ads ʔuhuy  What are you doing?  
Objects : 
tibu  table  
səxʷgʷ ədil  chair  
sɬagʷid  bed 
xʷuyu balʔtxʷ store  
talə(h)al ʔtxʷ bank  
Sentences:  
ʔuʔibəš čəd dxʷ ʔal ti ______.  I am walking to the _______.  
ʔutəlawil č əd dxʷ ʔal ti____.  I am running to the _______.  
ʔəsgʷədil čəd ʔal ti ______.  I am sitting on the ________.  
ʔəsʔitut č əd  I’m sleeping.  
ʔuʔəɬəd čəd  I’m eating.  
ʔuqʷu ʔqʷaʔdid č əd ʔə ti____.  I am drinking ________ . 
ʔukʷukʷcut č əd ʔə ti ______.  I am cooking ________.  
 
You may have noticed there are prefixes added when co nstructing a sentence. The 
ʔu- in the front adds –ing to the verb. The ʔəs- prefix is known as a state of being , 
which also adds an –ing to the verb.
